{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"@nicoespeon's blog","subtitles":{"en":"I write about web development, agile practices and personal organization.","fr":"Jâ€™Ã©cris sur le dÃ©veloppement web, les pratiques agiles et lâ€™organisation personnelle."},"author":{"name":"Nicolas Carlo","twitter":"nicoespeon"},"disqusShortname":"nicoespeon","url":"https://www.nicoespeon.com"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"c9ed23f9-1cd2-5e9a-b615-5d5f4c6e5e92","html":"<p>Today <em>aha moment</em> is cooking related ğŸ‘¨â€ğŸ³</p>\n<p>I usually use parchment paper to protect baking sheets and the likeâ€”essentially when I bake cakes, cookies, and other niceties ğŸª</p>\n<p>Sometimes, I also struggle to make it fit the recipient. Especially when it goes 3D. I used to measure and cut to adapt. But overall, itâ€™s not really convenient.</p>\n<figure>\n\t\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 431px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 139.21113689095125%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"using parchment paper\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/using-parchment-paper-3753dce8f49f09f635f641018a06ad97-11fd1.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/using-parchment-paper-3753dce8f49f09f635f641018a06ad97-f902b.jpg 240w,\n/static/using-parchment-paper-3753dce8f49f09f635f641018a06ad97-11fd1.jpg 431w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 431px) 100vw, 431px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <figcaption>Making the paper fits the recipient properly can be painful. Credits <a href=\"https://thepioneerwoman.com/food-and-friends/7-reasons-to-use-parchment-paper/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">The Pioneer Woman</a>.</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Today, I learned that you can actually <strong>wet the parchment paper and crumple it</strong> to make this easy! Parchment paper is strong, even when itâ€™s wet. Crumple it, put it under water, press it to eliminate the excess of water then unfold it. It will be easier to make it fit the recipient you want to protect.</p>\n<p>Also, I learned that you can use it almost any time a recipe tells you to put some butter on your cake mold. Wet parchment paper will do the trick faster and leave the mold in a cleaner stateâ€”so you can reuse more quickly if you need to.</p>\n<p>And voilÃ !</p>\n<figure>\n\t\n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 717px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 77.26638772663877%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"I like parchment paper\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/i-like-parchment-paper-da4fecb2a0e3f1aba5ff72ffdb971dd5-36000.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/i-like-parchment-paper-da4fecb2a0e3f1aba5ff72ffdb971dd5-f4d17.jpg 240w,\n/static/i-like-parchment-paper-da4fecb2a0e3f1aba5ff72ffdb971dd5-31063.jpg 480w,\n/static/i-like-parchment-paper-da4fecb2a0e3f1aba5ff72ffdb971dd5-36000.jpg 717w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 717px) 100vw, 717px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <figcaption>Credits <a href=\"https://altonbrown.com/parchment-paper-vs-wax-paper/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Alton&#xA0;Brown</a>.</figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p><strong>And you, do you have tips &#x26; tricks for cooking?</strong></p>","fields":{"tagSlugs":["/tags/til/","/tags/cooking/"],"slug":"/en/2019/